
[1]deride

   DERIDE, v.t. [L. To laugh.] To laugh at in contempt; to turn to
   ridicule or make sport of; to mock; to treat with scorn by laughter.

   The Pharisees also-derided him. Luke 16.

   Some, who adore Newton for his fluxions, deride him for his religion.
